Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.72,0:00:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, come back here, come back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.50,0:00:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you who are trying to escape, come back here, we have your number.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.06,0:00:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Number 292, you're going to get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.57,0:00:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine if you were part of that Olympic festival,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.92,0:00:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,7,000 people and everybody moves like this and you go like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.44,0:00:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Never heard from again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.50,0:00:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Motivation is so profoundly important.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.07,0:00:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And yes, we thought of two funny stories or one funny story.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.46,0:00:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This 4th of July parade is going by and everybody, this is in America,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.14,0:00:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,4th of July parade goes by, the troops, one idiot is out of step with all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.00,0:00:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And the mother sitting in the audience says, look, they're all out of step except Herbert.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.20,0:01:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That's America.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.43,0:01:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,America, they're all out of step except Herbert.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.51,0:01:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention is profoundly important.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.73,0:01:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The athlete, the athlete, of course, what's his motivation?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.73,0:01:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we saw the crowd was to be part of the one, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.84,0:01:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But the athlete, isn't he just looking for me, me, me?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.28,0:01:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, and there we made a major discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.09,0:01:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The athlete who?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.12,0:01:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Runs for the athlete who runs for out of runs for the sake of his country,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.51,0:01:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,his college, his class, his wife, his children, the athlete who runs for the sake of a higher good.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.43,0:02:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the name of the university, the country that the athlete will do his will do him will do them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.53,0:02:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The athlete.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.56,0:02:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The athlete who runs for the goodness of others has over 0.8 seconds, 0.9 seconds, one second is a nine tenths of a second lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.11,0:02:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see two runners.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.90,0:02:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,One is running for the university or running for the China or running for the pride of Germany, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.77,0:02:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the starting gun, the one with the higher motivation already has nine tenths of a second lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.37,0:02:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that something to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.88,0:02:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.31,0:02:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.50,0:02:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, there we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.00,0:03:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So it influences our performance, the intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.30,0:03:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you look at the intention behind your performances, always look for a higher good to which you can see yourself blending into and increasing your joy and the significance and the meaning of what you are doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.68,0:03:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, if you invent a better gadget, it's to make other people happy, convenient, be kind to the housewives' fingers, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.40,0:03:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If the chopper chops it, then she won't chop her fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.46,0:03:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So you think of all the wives who won't cut themselves on the paring knife with this chopping machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.40,0:03:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, try to hold the highest motivation you can behind all of your efforts to do it for the glory of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.13,0:03:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,God, of course, is the highest of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.21,0:03:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So those who dedicate all of their energies and efforts to Thee, O Lord, Most High.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.05,0:04:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we give this lecture, we do it in the name of Thee, O Lord, Most High.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.25,0:04:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thee, O Lord, Most High.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.25,0:04:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the very beginning, we state, we make a declaration of our intention that a group such as this meets for the glory of God and to reflect that glory in all its ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.75,0:04:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And we carry that into the daily world and by our reverence for life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.56,0:04:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have reverence for all that exists, all that exists, even if we don't understand why it exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.13,0:04:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why the Komoda dragon is what he is, but he serves some kind of an evolutionary purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.68,0:04:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we revere all of life and all of its expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.19,0:04:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And by doing that, the beauty of all that exists reveals itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.56,0:05:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In this lifetime, the beauty of all that exists revealed itself very suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.44,0:05:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Very suddenly, from an ordinary state of consciousness, it's like the veil was removed and I was stunned, speechless, and thoughtless.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.73,0:05:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It took years to think again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.55,0:05:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Think again, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.73,0:05:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I began to realize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.97,0:05:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That even thoughts can be of a higher purpose and it's okay to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.00,0:05:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,My respects to Wang Po.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.75,0:05:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people here are familiar with Wang Po?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.24,0:05:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.54,0:05:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.33,0:05:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people are not familiar with Wang Po?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.31,0:05:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Boo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.89,0:05:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Boo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.63,0:05:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Poo-poo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.67,0:05:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Wang Po was one of my heroes when I was young.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.04,0:06:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates and Pileo and Wang Po were my heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.13,0:06:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people were into baseball, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.35,0:06:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Socking a bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.56,0:06:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you about my childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.14,0:06:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the coach told me to stay off the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.88,0:06:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, they'll break you up in small pieces, the first tackle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.70,0:06:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I was forbidden to go out on the field during contact sports, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.12,0:06:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And the doctor wouldn't approve me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.19,0:06:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, with clavicles like that, they'll bust the first time somebody bucks you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.07,0:06:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I was stuck with Wang Po and Plato and Socrates and Euripides and all those old-fashioned people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.07,0:06:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.10,0:07:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm glad I'm not running for office, is all I can say, because I understand if you're wrinkled and old.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.92,0:07:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I got the biggest kick out of those political blogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.45,0:07:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He's old and he's wrinkled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.27,0:07:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And has white hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.22,0:07:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you don't want to vote for somebody who has white hair and is old and wrinkled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.62,0:07:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.75,0:07:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But I thought that is so funny, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.69,0:07:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That would get rid of, you know, some of the greatest minds in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.68,0:07:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you get wrinkled, they throw you away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.36,0:07:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I go to the beauty parlor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.16,0:07:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a wrinkle there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.33,0:07:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.81,0:07:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.81,0:07:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we've talked previously about allegiance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.86,0:07:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Allegiance is no longer to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.45,0:07:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Allegiance is to a popularity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.00,0:07:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's moral.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.62,0:08:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a more elaborate term.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.86,0:08:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a dedication to an ism.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.49,0:08:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Environmental ism.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.99,0:08:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Environmental ism.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.87,0:08:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Environmental ism will eventually kill all of life on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.16,0:08:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If you care to, it's also an extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.83,0:08:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,All that carbon in the atmosphere is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.37,0:08:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for all the carbon and the cow flatus and the prairies,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.13,0:08:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,life would come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.63,0:08:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's so funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.87,0:08:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.35,0:08:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Allegiance to isms.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.13,0:08:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And I point out in many lectures, you know, the book Extraordinary Popular Delusions
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.39,0:08:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Madness of Crowds, you know, because of its recurrent meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.17,0:08:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that everybody believes it doesn't have anything to do with the fact that it's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.10,0:08:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,truthful or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.17,0:08:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, and global warming is probably the biggest current illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.29,0:08:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very popular, so everybody's in for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.37,0:09:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But, of course, what we've taught in previous lectures is now scientifically validated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.98,0:09:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, this week it said the temperature of the Earth is due to cyclic changes in the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.20,0:09:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,surface magnetic activity of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.15,0:09:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We said that a few years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.49,0:09:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'd just like to see confirmation because otherwise you sound like a madman.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.92,0:09:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You sound like a nut.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.66,0:09:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm a respectable nut.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.24,0:09:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a doctor's degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.75,0:09:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.63,0:09:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The other thing that's currently popular, these extraordinary delusions become very
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.32,0:09:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,popular, and they become dominant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.84,0:09:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You wonder how society even survives.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.67,0:09:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.70,0:09:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Frequently, it doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.12,0:09:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind has been at war 93% of past time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.50,0:09:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the current, the other current popular delusion other than environmentalism is cultural
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.77,0:09:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Marxism.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.84,0:10:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Cultural Marxism is now very popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.25,0:10:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has to do with victim perpetrator delusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.58,0:10:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.75,0:10:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,See, Karl Marx, you see on the calibrated levels of the consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.53,0:10:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all in the mid to high 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.27,0:10:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And Marx calibrated at 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.70,0:10:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So he stands out like a sore thumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.60,0:10:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.01,0:10:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And cultural Marxism.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.94,0:10:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.13,0:10:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.51,0:10:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.70,0:10:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And cultural Marxism is now, the refined Marxism with the name Marx is removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.72,0:10:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And is the product now of a philosophic school, German philosophic school, the Frankfurt School.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.00,0:10:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Frankfurt School then taught all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.74,0:10:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So the modern universities are an output of cultural Marxism by virtue of Herbert Marcus.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.29,0:10:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So all of them calibrate like 180 or 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.65,0:11:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the modern university. This is an exceptional university. This is a division of NAU, and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.67,0:11:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we find that the community colleges now calibrate in the 400s, and the great universities calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.17,0:11:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200. All the great universities with the great names all calibrate below 200. Let's
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.00,0:11:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,see if that's true. All the great name, what do you call those universities? Ivy League.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.78,0:11:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All calibrate below 200. All calibrate below 200. The rise and fall of civilizations then
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.55,0:11:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes apparent that a new mass delusion overtakes the populace. Harvard, Yale, Princeton,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.42,0:11:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,all the great universities calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.66,0:12:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad I don't have any college-age kids. But if I did, I'd send them to this college,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.63,0:12:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, because this college calibrates around 440. So, not being a populace. So they target
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.75,0:12:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,these great universities because of the power of their name. So, propagandists know that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.02,0:12:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the name Harvard will impress lots of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.46,0:12:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yale.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.75,0:12:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yale, Princeton, you see. What's the name of this college here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.84,0:12:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yavapai.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.12,0:12:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yavapai College. Could you get elected president if you went to Yavapai College? You'd be out
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.87,0:12:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of step with the popular world. With the popular world, it calibrates 170. Steel doesn't melt,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.52,0:13:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 160. I hate to say it, but steel does melt. That's how they make railroad ties,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.78,0:13:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,railroad ties.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.09,0:13:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see this endless struggle for dominance and for control. So, politics is all about
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.10,0:13:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the struggle for dominance and the struggle for control. Once you have dominance and struggle
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.65,0:13:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and control, you can then milk it for zillions of dollars. What always amazes me is this politician
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.22,0:13:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,has been sued or raided.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.34,0:13:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.34,0:13:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.34,0:13:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He's been arrested, pulled away, et cetera, for, you know, taking massive bribery, you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.10,0:13:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,know, Alaska let's say or some place. And then what amazes me is the next election he's
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.01,0:13:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,reelected.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.01,0:14:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Put away for fraud, skulldudgery, high crimes and misdemeanors, and he's reelected.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.39,0:14:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, Socrates' dictum is that a democracy is something that we should also not control.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.58,0:14:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.58,0:14:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.75,0:14:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.59,0:14:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just going to talk a little bit more about our history.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.41,0:14:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot last more than a couple hundred years. Our democracy is what, 300 years old?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.23,0:14:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That rarely, in fact practically never, does a democracy last more than two or
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.25,0:14:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,three hundred years, because the people cannot tell truth from falsehood, because
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.90,0:14:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,they are so easily deceived by the wolf in sheep's clothing. Anything that's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.98,0:14:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,plausible, and especially with today's media, you can be brainwashed
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.34,0:14:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,innocently while you're brushing your teeth. When you're brushing your teeth,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.94,0:14:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you're being brainwashed. Always turn your TV off when you're brushing your
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.79,0:15:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,teeth, because you're being controlled, you're being manipulated. So the mind of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.03,0:15:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,modern man then has not only fallen to a critical level, but it is susceptible. And
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.45,0:15:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,this is because of the inner innocence of the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.85,0:15:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,child, the innocence of the child. So mankind has intuited this, and throughout
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.27,0:15:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,time has sought great teachers. Those are the great teachers, Jesus Christ, and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.91,0:15:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates, and Buddha, and Moses, and the great teachers of all time. So
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.13,0:15:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,when traditional wisdom was revered, you were somewhat protected
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.72,0:15:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,from modern fallacy and nonsense, because it was always compared in the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.47,0:15:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,back your mind with the teaching of Jesus Christ, or Socrates, or some
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.46,0:16:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,great being. And without a traditional education now, there is no inner
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.08,0:16:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,guideline. There is no inner guideline. So we see the Marxist ideology projected
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.85,0:16:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,onto all of society,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.58,0:16:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Marxist duality is perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.46,0:16:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that indoctrination, the minority is always the victim of the majority.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.46,0:16:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way Marx looked at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.01,0:16:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have the victim now, the victimology.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.92,0:16:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And the moral high ground is to claim yourself a greater victim than somebody else.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.59,0:16:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm glad wrinkled old men are getting to be victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.55,0:16:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Gives me a shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.50,0:16:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Gives me a shot at being victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.77,0:16:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.12,0:17:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to wait a long time to be victim, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.81,0:17:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so what's the appeal?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.23,0:17:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You say to yourself, what is the appeal of politics?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.32,0:17:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Aside from the juice that they get out of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.84,0:17:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it's obviously the struggle for democracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.97,0:17:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Some dominance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.88,0:17:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And the inner narcissism projected onto the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.81,0:17:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We mentioned the nine-tenths of a second advantage, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.35,0:17:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we did mention that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.74,0:17:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to make sure I didn't forget that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.58,0:17:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, whether you're a liberal or a conservative
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.01,0:17:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is partly a reflection of your age.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.21,0:17:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not a liberal when you're young, you've got no heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.99,0:17:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're still a liberal when you're old, you've got no brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.13,0:18:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's because the mind is struck by the glamour of causes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.22,0:18:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's say environmentalism is a laudatory cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.41,0:18:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody wants to get on the bandwagon
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.43,0:18:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and prevent cattle from passing gas on the plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.63,0:18:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.74,0:18:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.64,0:18:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Surreptitiously, they pass methane, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.50,0:18:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the environmentalists want us all to become vegetarians,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.29,0:18:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and that'll stop the cattle flatus from...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.05,0:18:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.44,0:18:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,...contaminating.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.79,0:18:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you do on a subway car, but anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.42,0:18:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.92,0:18:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.69,0:18:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.86,0:18:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.97,0:18:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.45,0:18:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's proof versus spoof.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.30,0:18:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.95,0:18:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Proof versus spoof.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.97,0:19:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.63,0:19:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The media are experts at spoof and how to program you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.95,0:19:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you'll believe the exact opposite of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.03,0:19:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And once you know how to calibrate things, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.29,0:19:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it's fun to watch the daily news and calibrate what is the level
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.46,0:19:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of that testimony, that witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.81,0:19:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Did that person commit that crime or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.29,0:19:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they guilty or not guilty?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.75,0:19:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the body under the cement slab?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.73,0:19:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.15,0:19:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you can't tell others about what you've discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.31,0:19:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So the other thing about our technique for telling truth from falsehood is discretion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.74,0:19:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,People do not welcome truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.16,0:19:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,People do not welcome truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.22,0:19:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They welcome what they have a narcissistic investment in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.98,0:19:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They are not interested in truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.85,0:19:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you want to get yourself killed, just go around spouting truth everywhere you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.36,0:20:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lucky if you get across the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.53,0:20:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.81,0:20:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is not popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.66,0:20:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.57,0:20:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What's popular is popularity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.96,0:20:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.85,0:20:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.56,0:20:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What's popular?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.45,0:20:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So everyone wants to be part of the crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.22,0:20:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody, it's, so it's really the herd instinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.45,0:20:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we view mankind then with his limitations and his evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.43,0:20:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the animal kingdom, then we see what captivates the mind of most of humanity,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.39,0:20:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,most of the time, is the herd instinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.39,0:20:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If everybody believes that, if everybody believes the cattle flatus is going to bring the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.56,0:20:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to a halt, then you can see how you become a vegetarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.78,0:20:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, what's the death rate of vegetarians?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.55,0:21:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All the vegetarians I ever knew are dead, so I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.61,0:21:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They used to be, all the health nuts I ever knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.07,0:21:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.07,0:21:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.07,0:21:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And I used to, I've told you about them before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.75,0:21:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We call them the brown baggers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.09,0:21:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And they would all sit in the back of the lunchroom, you know, and they had a brown bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.02,0:21:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And in there, there was organic brown rice.
