Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.49,0:31:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no successful still existing culture that does not acknowledge the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.50,0:31:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity of divinity some people try to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.98,0:31:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,substitute the state but then what do they worship they worship the state when they worship the state and usually they do worship it as it is in living beings now but then what do they worship they worship the state
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.69,0:31:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you worship communism, the state of communism,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.28,0:31:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,or whether you worship divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.69,0:31:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you're still worshiping something greater than your personal self.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.13,0:31:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's already a step.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.89,0:31:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you do it for the communist ideal,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.53,0:31:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,then workers, you have nothing to lose but your chains,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.29,0:31:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes uplifting.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.25,0:31:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Becomes uplifting.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.22,0:31:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So a thing is not either this or that in and of itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.96,0:31:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but what we make of it and how we comprehend it
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.83,0:31:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and how we contextualize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.14,0:31:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So context makes all the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.96,0:31:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's context that makes a difference about that nine-tenths of a second starting delay.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.85,0:32:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When the gun fires off, nine-tenths of a second,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.42,0:32:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you've just missed winning the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.59,0:32:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Just missed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.40,0:32:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You've just...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.75,0:32:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Nine-tenths of a second, you've just lost the hundred-yard dash.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.30,0:32:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So how does mankind get into such a difficult interpretation?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.48,0:32:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The defectiveness of humankind makes you humble.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.70,0:32:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the example of what I call the lying eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.58,0:32:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take witnesses of a crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.30,0:32:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.82,0:32:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They show the pictures of all these various criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.15,0:32:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The identification of the guilty person is fallacious 50% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.51,0:32:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a great project to free prisoners on death row.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.20,0:33:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was very important because the guys on death row,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.74,0:33:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because he was identified by two or three witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.05,0:33:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,then it turns out all of them were lying eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.59,0:33:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The lying eyes, calibrate, it occurs, let's see, what percent of the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.83,0:33:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Identification of criminal suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.53,0:33:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Witnesses are wrong over 50% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.21,0:33:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,50% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.91,0:33:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,55% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.76,0:33:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,50% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.94,0:33:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,50% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.75,0:33:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Three people say, I saw him do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.09,0:33:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he's in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.22,0:33:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And 50% of the time, he's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.57,0:33:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And even your own perception, you can't trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.33,0:33:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's going to be a mess after this lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.48,0:33:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't tell truth from spoof.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.50,0:33:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't believe your own lying eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.66,0:34:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't trust wrinkled old men.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.44,0:34:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.33,0:34:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.03,0:34:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we arrive at this?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.51,0:34:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there are several explanations.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.80,0:34:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably the most profound of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.61,0:34:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and the one that I tend to agree with,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.36,0:34:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is the effect of karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.15,0:34:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.84,0:34:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The most profound effect of all is karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.25,0:34:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Most profound effect of all is karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.67,0:34:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And say, well, Christianity doesn't believe in karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.61,0:34:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Western civilization doesn't believe in karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.65,0:34:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Christianity does believe in karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.07,0:34:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the Garden of Eden.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.40,0:34:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for the garden, the fall of man in the garden,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.67,0:34:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of Eden, you wouldn't need a savior.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.98,0:34:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There wouldn't be any sin, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.01,0:35:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the problem in the Garden of Eden?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.88,0:35:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is usually presented as disobedience of God's edict,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.94,0:35:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,not the eat of the tree of wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.32,0:35:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.53,0:35:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But the serpent came along and said to the woman,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.28,0:35:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.96,0:35:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.21,0:35:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.59,0:35:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.53,0:35:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And she did.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.15,0:35:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the fall of man.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.09,0:35:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they noticed they had no clothes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.44,0:35:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And they were naked and hid in shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.13,0:35:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So how did that come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.82,0:35:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What explains the fall of man in that historic tradition?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.51,0:35:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it evil?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.05,0:35:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it disobedience?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.61,0:35:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.05,0:35:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I see the innocence of Eve.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.80,0:35:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What the serpent knew was the innocence,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.42,0:35:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the inner innocence of the child,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.13,0:35:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the serpent said, oh, it'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.75,0:36:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.28,0:36:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a fine thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.51,0:36:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the serpent wasn't saying defy God.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.51,0:36:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The serpent was saying to the inner child in Eve,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.42,0:36:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,trust me, everything will be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.28,0:36:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.00,0:36:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was the beginning in the Christian tradition then.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.78,0:36:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So when they say Christianity doesn't believe,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.07,0:36:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,believe in karma, don't you believe them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.94,0:36:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't for original sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.50,0:36:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Garden of Eden, there wouldn't be any need for penance.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.42,0:36:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There wouldn't be any need for penance.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.28,0:36:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There'd be nothing to feel guilty about.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.78,0:36:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'd all be enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.03,0:36:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd all be enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.90,0:36:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the serpent then was the source of falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.84,0:36:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So falsehood came in and spoofed Eve's innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.00,0:36:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And being herself an innocent woman,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.53,0:37:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,why should she suspect that the serpent was up to some nefarious intention?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.86,0:37:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why I teach about the serpent,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.57,0:37:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to beware of the serpent.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.44,0:37:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Beware of the serpent.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.17,0:37:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that which is cunning and sly and deceptive
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.51,0:37:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to be able to sense where you're vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.09,0:37:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And that vulnerability, again,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.69,0:37:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is that intrinsically,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.67,0:37:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we all have the innocence of the child within us.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.75,0:37:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The pure subjectivity of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.11,0:37:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The structure of the mind is such
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.51,0:37:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that it cannot tell one from another.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.61,0:37:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The computer, the mind's computer,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.48,0:37:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,can become programmed with falsehood as easily so.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.34,0:37:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We all have intrinsically the innocence of the computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.96,0:37:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The computer doesn't say,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.84,0:37:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, I think I'll record.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.00,0:37:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll record this and not record this.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.90,0:38:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The computer of the human mind
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.21,0:38:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically records all that it is presented with.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.42,0:38:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it's fallacious or true.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.42,0:38:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no means of discernment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.48,0:38:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual evolution then comes from
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.59,0:38:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,studying advanced spiritual teachings
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.84,0:38:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and advancing by intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.42,0:38:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So by one's intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.46,0:38:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,one already is progressing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.53,0:38:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Already progressing by virtue of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.86,0:38:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when one reaches a certain level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.86,0:38:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is the sheep's clothing
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.05,0:38:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which is innocence become apparent.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.05,0:38:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's at level 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.09,0:38:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,At level 600, the third eye of the Buddhic body
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.09,0:38:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is what it's classically called.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.09,0:38:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one of the etheric bodies above the crown chakra.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.09,0:38:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It opens and now one instantly can recognize falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.11,0:39:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And deception.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.11,0:39:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,From that time on, you're protected.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.11,0:39:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You're protected by the presence of the divine spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.11,0:39:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in the capacity to discern essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.19,0:39:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the story of the Garden of Eden.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.63,0:39:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the innocence,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.19,0:39:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the innocence then,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.19,0:39:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ taught that sin is nothing but primarily ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.09,0:39:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sin is ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.09,0:39:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Sin is error.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.13,0:39:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So the original meaning of the term sin
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.13,0:39:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is error, error.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.13,0:39:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,To be in error.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.19,0:39:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,To realize the innocence of the inner child
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.00,0:39:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of everyone who exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.00,0:39:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives us a capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.11,0:39:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to be forgiving towards all people no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.57,0:39:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So the person who thinks that he's doing God a favor,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.01,0:40:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,worshiping God,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.01,0:40:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,by killing me,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.01,0:40:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because I'm a non-believer,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.65,0:40:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I still recognize the validity of his intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.88,0:40:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If the way to worship God is to kill all non-believers,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.94,0:40:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,then I can see the innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.94,0:40:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I differ with the correctness of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.75,0:40:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but I can see the innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.75,0:40:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So if he kills you,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.36,0:40:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you just say it's okay, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.36,0:40:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.84,0:40:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.84,0:40:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you about a past life I remember during the Crusades.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.34,0:40:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And this same entity and I have had interactions over many lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.34,0:40:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And I killed him for Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.57,0:40:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and he killed me for Allah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.57,0:40:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It was during the Crusades.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.57,0:40:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Through and through,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.57,0:40:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and through and through,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.57,0:40:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and we both fell over,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.57,0:41:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and our etheric body went out of the physical body,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.57,0:41:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and we broke out laughing at each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.57,0:41:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, I did it for Allah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.44,0:41:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, I did it for Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.44,0:41:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we laughed and laughed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.44,0:41:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The naivety of the human mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.44,0:41:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of his devotion to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.78,0:41:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,he killed me, and I acknowledge that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.78,0:41:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, I've had great respect for that entity.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.07,0:41:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And we killed each other for God and for...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.07,0:41:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So even those who blow us up,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.17,0:41:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,even those who blow us up,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.17,0:41:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,if they are doing it from that intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.51,0:41:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I can forgive them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.51,0:41:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I'm not going to hang out with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.26,0:41:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Or invite them to lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.73,0:41:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it we're supposed to do with those people?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.73,0:41:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's some politically correct thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.86,0:41:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We're supposed to accommodate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.86,0:41:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.92,0:41:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.92,0:42:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Let other people accommodate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.92,0:42:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, I'm going to eat in a different restaurant
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.92,0:42:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,than where they hang out.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.92,0:42:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This may be the day they're going to blow up the restaurant
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.92,0:42:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to get rid of all these...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.92,0:42:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth depends on context.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.92,0:42:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The overall intention then sets an overall field.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.96,0:42:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So the nonlinear sets the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.96,0:42:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether a thing is good or evil cannot be discerned
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.96,0:42:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,by looking at the thing itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.96,0:42:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but only in context.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.96,0:42:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Only in context.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.15,0:42:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we have in today's society, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.44,0:42:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the conspiracy theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.44,0:42:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and the logic-proof delusional disorder.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.44,0:42:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So many of society's problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.44,0:42:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they say they closed the mental hospitals many years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.44,0:42:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That was also cultural Marxism.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.50,0:42:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It came through a guy named Thomas Szasz,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.59,0:42:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,popularized it,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.59,0:42:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to say that mental illness was only a label.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.59,0:43:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, they closed all the mental hospitals.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.07,0:43:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So all the people who are dangerous
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.07,0:43:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,are now wandering the street
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.07,0:43:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and killing people right and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.07,0:43:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So it used to be out of compassion
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.13,0:43:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that you protected people
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.13,0:43:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,from their own limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.13,0:43:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I could tell them,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.23,0:43:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,if I let this guy out,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.23,0:43:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I know exactly what he's going to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.23,0:43:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't just the safety of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.23,0:43:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So the criteria was
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.23,0:43:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that this person is safe with his own self,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.23,0:43:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity to survive
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.23,0:43:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and look after your own basic needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.23,0:43:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So some we kept in the hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.23,0:43:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,until they got well enough
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.23,0:43:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that they could survive on their own,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.23,0:43:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that they had enough wits.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.23,0:43:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They could survive on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.23,0:43:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So it wasn't just because of labeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.23,0:43:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It was survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.23,0:43:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So now they become drug addicted
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.23,0:43:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and hang out on the sidewalk
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.23,0:43:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and commit crimes
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.23,0:44:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and get murdered and murder each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.23,0:44:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And they all end up in jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.23,0:44:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So we saw the bottom of the list
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.23,0:44:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of the levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.23,0:44:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The average consciousness in prison
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.23,0:44:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is around 65, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.23,0:44:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.23,0:44:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The average consciousness in prison
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.23,0:44:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is around 65.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.23,0:44:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's the correct number.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.23,0:44:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness level 65.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.23,0:44:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Can a person survive out there
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.59,0:44:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,with a consciousness level of 65?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.59,0:44:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of humanitarian consideration,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.59,0:44:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd say this person needs to be protected
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.59,0:44:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,until they're more capable
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.59,0:44:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of protecting themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.59,0:44:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,remembering to take their medication,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.59,0:44:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,remembering to see the doctor,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.59,0:44:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,staying out of the way of crime, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.71,0:44:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So the intention then
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.71,0:44:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is the good and the welfare of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.78,0:44:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The good and the welfare of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.78,0:44:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.78,0:44:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So the one spiritual dictum
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.78,0:44:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that we stay by
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.78,0:44:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is out of love and consideration
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.78,0:44:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and reverence for all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.78,0:45:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And let that be the overall context
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.78,0:45:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of your own volition.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.84,0:45:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason we do all that we do
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.84,0:45:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is for the good of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.84,0:45:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If you will say,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.84,0:45:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,what can I do to help the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.94,0:45:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you could stay out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.94,0:45:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Get off the highway now.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.67,0:45:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention then, the intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.67,0:45:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.19,0:45:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So we showed by the chart we showed,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.19,0:45:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,or the pyramid,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.19,0:45:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it's what you have become
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.19,0:45:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that compensates for the negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.19,0:45:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So the negativity of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.48,0:45:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,would be so overwhelming
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.48,0:45:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it would destroy mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.48,0:45:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,except for people like yourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.48,0:45:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.48,0:45:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize that without you,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.48,0:45:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,millions would die.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.48,0:45:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.53,0:45:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Without this crowd here assembled.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.53,0:45:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This crowd here assembled.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.53,0:45:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.96,0:46:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions would die.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.55,0:46:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions would die
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.55,0:46:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,were it not because in the pyramid
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.55,0:46:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,there's that small top.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.55,0:46:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's the balance,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.55,0:46:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the little bitty pyramid over here
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.55,0:46:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and the great mass of mankind here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.55,0:46:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To give greater worth and value.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.88,0:46:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That your spiritual work, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.88,0:46:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is not just for your own spiritual advancement.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.90,0:46:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But by seeking spiritual truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.15,0:46:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you are serving all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.15,0:46:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,By your own search for enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.63,0:46:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and for spiritual truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.63,0:46:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you are serving all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.90,0:46:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions would die,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.90,0:46:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,were it not for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.90,0:46:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,By your own search for enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.57,0:46:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you benefit all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.92,0:46:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You benefit all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.92,0:46:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The depiction of a Buddhist type meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.69,0:46:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is gazing at your own navel there,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.69,0:47:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,for is incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.69,0:47:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It is for the good and the welfare
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.65,0:47:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.65,0:47:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that we seek the highest truth
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.65,0:47:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and seek to become at one with that truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.65,0:47:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We seek to become
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.78,0:47:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the expression of that truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.94,0:47:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you pass all beautiful things,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.94,0:47:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you acknowledge their beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.94,0:47:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And at a certain level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.23,0:47:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to actually avoid that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.23,0:47:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the beauty of things
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.23,0:47:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,just knocks you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.23,0:47:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like a loving glance between two people,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.23,0:47:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.23,0:47:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It just makes you weep.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.23,0:47:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're careful not to look at the flowers
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.23,0:47:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're stunning perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.36,0:47:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.36,0:47:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That was created by God.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.09,0:47:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That was created by God.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.09,0:48:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That flower was created by God.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.94,0:48:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So you sense the divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.86,0:48:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,within all of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.86,0:48:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of reverence for divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.17,0:48:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you're then reverent towards all of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.17,0:48:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.25,0:48:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So as I use the example
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.25,0:48:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,from previous lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.44,0:48:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you say to the headsman,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.44,0:48:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,don't feel badly about what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.44,0:48:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your duty to the crown.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.44,0:48:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So you put your head on the block.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.98,0:48:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And as the headsman comes down,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.11,0:48:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you bless him.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.11,0:48:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You're doing your duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.71,0:48:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You recognize it's his honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.71,0:48:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's his honor that he serves the crown.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.71,0:48:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And people of that era,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.92,0:48:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a mark of honor to serve the crown
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.92,0:48:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than your own personal self.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.92,0:48:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So even the headsman,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.13,0:48:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,as he comes over,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.13,0:48:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you can bless him.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.13,0:49:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And you tell him,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.42,0:49:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,don't feel badly about what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.42,0:49:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a man of honor
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.42,0:49:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're serving the crown.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.42,0:49:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He goes home feeling happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.00,0:49:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Her wife says,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.00,0:49:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Harold, how'd it go today?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.00,0:49:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He says,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.07,0:49:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that was her answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.07,0:49:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How'd it go today, Harold?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.07,0:49:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Snap, off it goes, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.90,0:49:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've demonstrated
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.90,0:49:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,how if you live within the present instant,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.90,0:49:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,no such thing as a problem
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.03,0:49:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,can arise.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.44,0:49:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Every instant is complete
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.44,0:49:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and total within itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.44,0:49:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem can exist
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.69,0:49:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.69,0:49:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You have some illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.23,0:49:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, is it going to kill you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.23,0:50:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.23,0:50:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what are you sobbing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.23,0:50:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and crying about,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.23,0:50:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.23,0:50:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If you live in this instant,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.23,0:50:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,this instant now,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.23,0:50:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not capable of a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.34,0:50:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only when you project yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.34,0:50:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,into the future
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.34,0:50:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and fear and control
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.34,0:50:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or you project yourself into the past
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.34,0:50:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,with regret and blame and guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.65,0:50:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If you live in this instant,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.65,0:50:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,no problem is possible
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.92,0:50:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in this instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.92,0:50:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.59,0:50:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact, oh Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.09,0:50:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,God said.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.30,0:50:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.51,0:50:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, so,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.51,0:50:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,by understanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.42,0:50:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.42,0:50:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.42,0:50:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that all things come into being
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.55,0:50:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of that which they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.55,0:51:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.73,0:51:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole scientific view of causality
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.92,0:51:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is there's a this causing a this causing a this,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.92,0:51:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which goes back through time.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.92,0:51:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you check it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.92,0:51:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you find any single event
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.92,0:51:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,has 10 million causes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.92,0:51:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for this room,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.92,0:51:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,this couldn't be here,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.92,0:51:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be here right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.92,0:51:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We wouldn't be talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.92,0:51:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't be able to hear my voice, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.92,0:51:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes 10 million items
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.92,0:51:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to account for any occurrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.63,0:51:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All occurrences are happening spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.63,0:51:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of the evolution of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.63,0:51:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.63,0:51:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ultimate realization
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.21,0:51:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,or the teaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.21,0:51:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the purpose of our teaching
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.21,0:51:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is to bring to your awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.21,0:51:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is no one,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.21,0:51:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is no one doing what is happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.44,0:51:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The presumption of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.44,0:51:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is there is a me,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.44,0:51:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a separate I,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.44,0:52:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that is causing this to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.55,0:52:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A more advanced consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.55,0:52:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,if you catch it,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.55,0:52:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you will realize that that happened
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.55,0:52:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.55,0:52:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no personal self.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.09,0:52:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that my personal self?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.28,0:52:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Look in the mirror,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.28,0:52:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.28,0:52:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that me?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.26,0:52:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All that happens autonomously.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.26,0:52:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As a consequence of that which you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.26,0:52:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the content
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.67,0:52:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and the context is the level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.67,0:52:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no personal separate self,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.67,0:52:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,separate from the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.80,0:52:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one reason why
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.48,0:53:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,when you become a part of an Olympic demonstration,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.48,0:53:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a feeling of elation
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.48,0:53:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because at least momentarily
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.57,0:53:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you've escaped the narcissistic egotism
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.73,0:53:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and limitation of a personal I.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.73,0:53:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Being the star.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.73,0:53:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happening is now
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.21,0:53:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,selflessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.21,0:53:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The self with a capital S.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.21,0:53:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolving then.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.36,0:53:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So all things come about
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.36,0:53:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of the totality
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.36,0:53:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that has ever been
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.36,0:53:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,including that which you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.36,0:53:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.40,0:53:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no personal self
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.40,0:53:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a cause of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.40,0:53:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's no personal self
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.59,0:53:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a cause of anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.59,0:53:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,then what is the karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.59,0:53:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens to the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.59,0:53:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,deleterious karmic consequences?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.59,0:53:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't any.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.63,0:53:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You leave this world stupid,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.40,0:53:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you come back to the next life stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.40,0:54:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.51,0:54:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So evolution proceeds
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.51,0:54:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,over great expanses of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.51,0:54:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Great expanses of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.55,0:54:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And the karmic inheritance
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.55,0:54:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of propensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.65,0:54:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Propensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.65,0:54:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody is forced to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.65,0:54:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You're dealing with likelihoods.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.75,0:54:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So karmic propensities,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.75,0:54:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't speak of karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.75,0:54:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I speak of karmic propensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.75,0:54:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The inclination is to
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.78,0:54:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,get even with the son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.78,0:54:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He deserves it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.78,0:54:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And then,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.23,0:54:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because of spiritual training and interference,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.23,0:54:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.23,0:54:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps there is another way of looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.34,0:54:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Sermon on the mountain
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.76,0:54:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,flashes through your mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.96,0:54:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and you forgive him,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.96,0:54:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.96,0:54:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not pull the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.96,0:55:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not pull the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.96,0:55:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening within itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.92,0:55:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can picture yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.92,0:55:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I like picturing yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.92,0:55:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as a magnetic filing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.92,0:55:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And the will of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.92,0:55:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole field of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.92,0:55:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,its power is infinite, unlimited.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.92,0:55:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.03,0:55:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.03,0:55:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens within you
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.03,0:55:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and around you and to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.03,0:55:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is a consequence of what you have become
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.03,0:55:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,interacting in a field.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.03,0:55:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's a powerful magnetic field
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.03,0:55:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in which all of us are polarized.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.03,0:55:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This is our good side,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.03,0:55:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,our good karma side,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.03,0:55:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,our bad karma side.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.03,0:55:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We say, screw you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.03,0:55:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We go down to the bad karma side.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.03,0:55:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We say, oh yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.03,0:55:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but you couldn't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.03,0:55:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we go to the good karma side.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.03,0:55:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're constantly moving
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.03,0:55:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in this infinite field.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.30,0:55:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a field of propensities
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.30,0:55:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and likelihoods.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.30,0:55:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a field of causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.46,0:55:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you have the karma
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.46,0:56:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of some greatly negative thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.46,0:56:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not coerced.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.46,0:56:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.46,0:56:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So we all have within ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.46,0:56:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a spiritual freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.61,0:56:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We are always free to choose,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.61,0:56:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,choose differently this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.61,0:56:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.61,0:56:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We exist in a constant state
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.61,0:56:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.61,0:56:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Is she telling me the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.34,0:56:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We all live in a state
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.34,0:56:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of absolute inner freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.67,0:56:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in an energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.67,0:56:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,with infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.15,0:56:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we align with that power,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.15,0:56:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we then radiate out
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.15,0:56:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a goodness to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.15,0:56:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,which benefits all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.15,0:56:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So by alignment and by intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.28,0:56:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,a group such as this
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.28,0:56:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is profoundly affecting
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.28,0:56:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the lives of millions of people
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.28,0:56:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that should get rid of the question,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.69,0:57:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,what can I do to help the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.71,0:57:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.71,0:57:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Just be what you are
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.71,0:57:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to the fullest capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.71,0:57:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore you're fulfilling
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.71,0:57:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,God's will for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.71,0:57:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.98,0:57:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That is fulfilling God's will for you
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.98,0:57:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that each person become
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.98,0:57:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the most of which they can become.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.61,0:57:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,By fulfilling your potential then,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.61,0:57:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you are serving God
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.61,0:57:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and your fellow man.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.61,0:57:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And you are doing
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.61,0:57:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,all that you can for mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.80,0:57:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if that don't puff you up, babies,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.26,0:57:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that should last until lunchtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.67,0:57:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All you people out there
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.67,0:57:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,saving the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.67,0:57:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What time we do back, honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.67,0:57:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We resume at 2 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.15,0:57:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We resume at 2 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.15,0:57:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And avoid all sin
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.15,0:58:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,between now and 2 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.73,0:58:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
